cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with hyperspectral image classification using generative adversarial networks and probabilistic graphical models. The use of convolutional neural networks and conditional random fields also suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of unsupervised learning techniques, which may suggest the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of spectral-spatial characteristics of hyperspectral data may suggest the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of large amounts of unlabeled data may suggest the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
